ecologyNotes: talrig på skråning ned mod søen, 2-3 mycelier
notes: Samme mycelium som Niels Mogensens fund fra 12.08.2010. Se diskussionen der: Beskrivelse: Cortinarius “cf. rubellus” TB 10.xxx, Silkeborg Sønderskov, 22.08.2010, in quite natural beech forest on the slope towards Brassø, peninsula xxx, leg TB & Niels Mogensen, in fair quantity, probably two mycelia in one place, another about 200 m longer to the S. Photos: (TB) DSCN 4514, 4521 Pileus convex to somewhat campanulate, frequently somewhat lobed, tomentose, not genuinely squamulose, slightly subsquamulose at centre, margin opaque, very slightly subhygrophanous, brownish orange about Mu. 5YR5/6 outwards 4.5/4 to warmer than 5YR5/7 centre about 2.5YR4/5, in older specimen near 2.5YR3.5/6 about 32-48 mm wide.  Lamellae more or less close, narrowly emarginated, about 3.5 mm wide, slightly ventricose(fairly) thin, edge entire, glabrous, when young about 5YR5/5, at maturity more rusty brown, slightly darker than 2.5YR5.5/6. Stipe e.g. 70 x 17 mm, typically broadest in the middle and fusiform towards base, rarely subcylindrical, then e.g. 75 x 11 mm, sordid ochre- to reddish brown, dry and dull, lengthily (coarsely) fibrillose to cortina pale yellowish velum zones not very conspicuous, slightly paler than 10YR7/6. Context fairly thin in pileus, firm, concolorous under pileipellis elsewhere, downwards yellowish white, in stipe sordid ochre-brownish, slightly darker the next day. Smell indistinctly raphanoid, to indistinctly like extinguishing candle, or more like a moist cellar (the next day). Spore-print failed. Spores (14/1): (8.9-)9.1-9.8(-10.3) x 6.6-7.8 (-8.1) µm, shortly ellipsoid, less frequently subamygdaloid to ovoid, Av. = 9.5 x 7.3 µm, Q = (1.2-)1.25-1.35, Qav. = 1.31, some slightly thick-walled, warts distinct, small to medium, plage present.  The other collection was photographed, but not described, phot.:  Differs from C. rubellus (directly compared specimens growing under Picea abies nearby) in the following: Pileus shape variable and not prominently umbonate, lack of genuine scales, more or less paler. Lamellae paler at least when young, narrow. Stipe shape different. Spores about same size and shape, but warts partly coarser, with plage. Does not fit related, named species from N Europe, the French work is not yet studied. Fotos oploades senere

ecologyNotes: fugtig lavning, i mos
notes: hat spidspuklet, 5 cm (største frl), orangebrun, fibret, lameller orangebrune, stok 7,5 x 0,8-1,2 mm, udvidet og tilspidset nedad, med orangebrune slørrester på lysere baggrund. Ingen grønne toner i stokkødet. Lugt svagt ræddikeagtig. Sporer 9-10.5 x 6,5-8µm, gns. 9,7 x 7,2 mm. Bestemt med slørhatte-hjulnøglen. Mangler tydeligt zigzag-mønster i stokbælterne, men sporerne er for brede til lignende arter i nøgle G, kanelslørhatte, og fundet nøgler  til puklet giftsslørhat i nøgle H. 18 sporer af 20 målte er 7µm brede eller derover.
